üîê Ansible Vault Commands Cheat Sheet
1. Create a New Vault File
ansible-vault create secret.yml


üëâ Opens editor, lets you add encrypted content.

2. Encrypt an Existing File
ansible-vault encrypt file.yml

3. Decrypt an Encrypted File
ansible-vault decrypt secret.yml

4. Edit an Encrypted File
ansible-vault edit secret.yml


üëâ Opens editor to securely modify file.

5. View an Encrypted File
ansible-vault view secret.yml

6. Rekey (Change Password)
ansible-vault rekey secret.yml

7. Encrypt Multiple Files
ansible-vault encrypt file1.yml file2.yml

8. Decrypt Multiple Files
ansible-vault decrypt file1.yml file2.yml

9. Use Vault in Playbooks
ansible-playbook playbook.yml --ask-vault-pass


OR with a vault password file:

ansible-playbook playbook.yml --vault-password-file ~/.vault_pass.txt

10. Encrypt Only Variables

Instead of full file encryption:

ansible-vault encrypt_string 'MySecretPassword' --name 'db_password'


‚û°Ô∏è Generates YAML-safe encrypted variable.

11. Specify Vault ID (Multiple Keys)
ansible-vault encrypt --vault-id dev@prompt dev-vars.yml
ansible-vault encrypt --vault-id prod@prompt prod-vars.yml


Use with playbooks:

ansible-playbook playbook.yml --vault-id dev@prompt --vault-id prod@prompt

